events.name: Opening Ceremony
events.description: Join us to kick off our 10th Hackiversary! You can view the opening ceremony in Siebel 1404, CIF Auditorium or Study Steps, or online on our YouTube.

events.name: Friday Dinner
events.description: Portillo's will be hosted at Siebel 2nd floor and CIF 4th floor. Attendees will only be able to eat on the 4th floor of CIF and 1st/2nd floors in Siebel.

events.name: Friday Midnight Snack
events.description: Hungry? Join us for Insomnia Cookies at Siebel 2nd floor.

events.name: Saturday Breakfast
events.description: Come to Siebel 2nd floor and CIF 4th floor for a hearty breakfast from Einstein Bros. Bagels and great start to your day. Attendees will only be able to eat on the 4th floor of CIF and 1st/2nd floors in Siebel.

events.name: Saturday Lunch
events.description: Join us for Papa Johns at Siebel 2nd floor and CIF 4th floor. Attendees will only be able to eat on the 4th floor of CIF and 1st/2nd floors in Siebel.

events.name: Coffee Chat
events.description: Drink some coffee and meet some cool people at CIF 4th floor.

events.name: Saturday Dinner
events.description: Fuel your late night hacking with a yummy dinner from Potbelly at Siebel 2nd floor and CIF 4th floor. Attendees will only be able to eat on the 4th floor of CIF and 1st/2nd floors in Siebel.

events.name: Sunday Breakfast
events.description:
Join us for Einstein Bros. Bagels before the hackathon submission deadline for breakfast before judging starts. Breakfast locations are Siebel 2nd floor and CIF 4th floor. 

Attendees will only be able to eat on the 4th floor of CIF and 1st/2nd floors in Siebel.

events.name: Hacking Starts
events.description: Start working on your fabulous projects!

events.name: Project Submission Deadline
events.description: Projects are due! Make sure to get them submitted on Devpost.

events.name: Closing Ceremony
events.description: Join us to end our 10th Hackiversary and find out who won! You can view the closing ceremony in Siebel 1404, CIF Auditorium or Study Steps, or online on our YouTube.

events.name: Check-in
events.description: Check-in to HackIllinois at first floor of Siebel Center for Computer Science.

events.name: John Deere Company Showcase
events.description: Come learn more about professional opportunities at John Deere in Siebel 2405 from 8-9PM.

events.name: Intro to GIT & Team Matching
events.description: Learn how to use git and participate in a speed friending to find a team for Hackillinois 2023!

events.name: CIF CLOSES
events.description: CIF closes at 11PM.

events.name: Recruiter/Mentor Social
events.description: Mentors and recruiters, enjoy an evening at Legends Bar & Grill at 11:00 PM!

events.name: League Tournament
events.description: Ready to test your League skills? Register for our League Tournament that will be held at Siebel 2405 from 11PM - 2 AM.

events.name: SIEBEL CLOSES
events.description: Time to leave for the night! Siebel closes at 3AM.

events.name: CIF & SIEBEL OPENS
events.description: Buildings open at 7AM!

events.name: John Deere Lounge
events.description: Come to CIF 3038 to hang out with John Deere and chat about opportunities and anything else from 8:00 AM to 10:00 PM.

events.name: Scavenger Hunt
events.description: Have fun familiarizing yourself with Siebel and CIF and earn a bunch of points along the way! Scavenger hunt takes place from 3 - 5:30 PM in Siebel and CIF.

events.name: Company Expo
events.description: Check out professional opportunities from 4:00 - 5:30 PM at the Siebel 1st floor Atrium.

events.name: How To Build a Web App
events.description: Interested in learning how to build a web application? You've come to the right place! This event will take place in CIF 4035 from 9:30 AM to 10:30 AM.

events.name: Intro to Backend Programming
events.description: What is a database? How can you use one in your project? Learn more about implementing backend programming in this workshop co-hosted by Women in Computer Science, Hack4Impact, and Caterpillar. It’ll be CIF 4035 from 11:00 AM to 12:00 PM!

events.name: Mini Carnival
events.description: The theme of this year’s HackIllinois is carnival, so have fun participating in mini carnival games during this event! Activities will take place in Siebel 2nd floor atrium from 5:30 - 6:30 PM.

events.name: Code in the Dark
events.description: Replicate a webpage using HTML and CSS in the metaphorical dark! Event takes place in CIF 4035 from 8:30 - 9:30 PM.

events.name: CIF CLOSES
events.description: CIF closes at 11PM.

events.name: Mario-Kart
events.description: Chill out after a long day of hacking by playing Mario Kart! Event will be from 12 AM - 2 AM at Siebel 1404.

events.name: SIEBEL CLOSES
events.description: Time to leave for the night! Siebel closes at 3AM.

events.name: CIF & SIEBEL OPENS
events.description: Buildings open at 7AM!

events.name: Submission Office Hours
events.description: Get some last minute help on your projects from 7-8AM at Siebel outside ACM Office, CIF 3rd floor, or on Discord.

events.name: Project Showcase
events.description: Present your project to judges from 10:30 AM to 12:00 PM at Siebel 1st Floor, Siebel 2nd Floor, or CIF 3031.

events.name: Shark Tank
events.description: Watch or present a project pitch at CIF 4039 from 12:30 - 2:30 PM.

events.name: Buses Depart
events.description: Buses depart from Siebel at 5:00 PM.

events.name: How to Build an ML Model
events.description: Want to dive into the world of AI? Learn how to build a machine learning model with John Deere! Siebel 2405, 1:30PM to 2:30PM!
